Building pulseGUI
=================
Use the Makefile
$ make
This will create shared libraries in ROOT and exit

Running pulseGUI
================
$ root -l pulseGUI.C
This will load the shared libraries and start up the pulseGUI interface

Python tools
============
source setup.sh
# iv curve drawing and (incorrect) guesstimate of VBreak
ivAnalyze.py ivfilename
# reads in list of files w/ xx.xV field in filename and estimated VBreak
vbreak.py file1 file2 [file3] ...
vbreak.py path*

SVN overview:
============
Some Links:
http://svnbook.red-bean.com/
http://www.thegeekstuff.com/2011/04/svn-command-examples/
http://docs.codehaus.org/display/HAUSMATES/How+to+Organize+a+Subversion+Repository
http://docs.codehaus.org/display/HAUSMATES/How+to+Tag+and+Branch+a+Subversion+Repository
http://gcc.gnu.org/wiki/SvnTricks
http://root.cern.ch/drupal/content/subversion-howto

**Contact BH: to add you ssh key to access**


checkout (for development on trunk):
--------
$ svn co svn+ssh://svn@hepcat.phys.virginia.edu/home/svn/repo/pulseGUI/trunk pulseGUI [or other dirname] 

status
------
# see what's been done in the working directory
$ svn status

add file(s)
-----------
$ svn add filename(list)

commit
------
$ svn commit -m"comment string"

**IMPORTANT** The setup with sshkeys, logs all commits under the svn user.
In order to log changes by real user, please use comments like:
"BH: added cool functionality"
or
"TA: added new binary read format"

make a tag
----------
$ svn copy -m"comment string" \
  svn+ssh://svn@hepcat.phys.virginia.edu/home/svn/repo/pulseGUI/trunk \
  svn+ssh://svn@hepcat.phys.virginia.edu/home/svn/repo/pulseGUI/tags/<tag-name>

list available tags
-------------------
$ svn ls svn+ssh://svn@hepcat.phys.virginia.edu/home/svn/repo/pulseGUI/tags

checkout a tag
--------------
svn co svn+ssh://svn@hepcat.phys.virginia.edu/home/svn/repo/pulseGUI/tags <tagname> [dirname]

add exec bit after committing file
==================================
svn propset svn:executable ON <file>

